Wireshark Network Traffic Analysis Lab
Overview
This project demonstrates hands-on experience using Wireshark to analyze network traffic, inspect packet data, and apply filters to investigate communication between systems.

Tools Used
- Windows VM
- Wireshark
- Packet Capture (.pcap files)

Objectives
- Identify source and destination IP addresses
- Analyze network protocols (TCP, DNS, ICMP)
- Inspect packet layers and payload data
- Apply filters to isolate relevant traffic

Key Tasks Performed
- Applied filters such as:
  - ip.addr == 142.250.1.139
  - udp.port == 53
  - tcp.port == 80
  - tcp contains "curl"
- Analyzed DNS queries and responses
- Inspected TCP packet structure (ports, sequence numbers, flags)
- Examined packet layers: Ethernet, IPv4, TCP, Application

Key Findings
- Identified communication between internal and external IP addresses
- Observed DNS resolution process for domain queries
- Analyzed HTTP web requests and TCP communication patterns
- Used filtering to significantly reduce dataset and focus on relevant traffic

Skills Gained
- Network traffic analysis
- Packet inspection
- Protocol analysis (TCP/IP, DNS)
- Cybersecurity investigation techniques
